â€¢	Attach: Exhibits (dated), Proposed Order, COS.
 
9.2 Pro Se Deposition Checklist (You as Deponent)

Purpose. Reduce risk, preserve record, avoid volunteering.
When. Upon notice of deposition or subpoena.
Quick Win. The â€œFour Pâ€™sâ€: Pause â†’ Paraphrase â†’ Pinpoint â†’ Pass.

Checklist â€” Before
â€¢	Read the notice; calendar time limits; confirm location/remote rules
â€¢	Assemble binder: pleadings index, claims/elements sheet, errata template
â€¢	Define 3 protected zones: privilege, privacy orders, scope objections
â€¢	Practice 10 sample questions with a friend/ally (role play)

Checklist â€” During
â€¢	Listen fully â†’ Pause (2â€“3 sec)
â€¢	Paraphrase the question if ambiguous
â€¢	Answer only what was asked; Pinpoint memory (â€œI recall that on [date]â€¦â€)
â€¢	If improper: â€œObjection, form; I will answer unless instructed otherwiseâ€
â€¢	Pass if you do not know or do not recall; do not guess

Checklist â€” After
â€¢	Review transcript; complete errata with reasons; serve timely
â€¢	Log any admissions by examiner; map to elements

Field Card (print)
â€¢	Answers end with a period.
â€¢	â€œIf you have the document, please show it to me.â€
â€¢	Use dates, not adjectives.

Pitfalls
â€¢ Volunteering narrative. â€¢ Accepting examinerâ€™s summary as your own.
Cross Refs. FG Evidence cards; LCa Discovery Containment; JC Discovery Stays.
 
9.3 Rules of Evidence â€” Quick Objection Cards

Purpose. Pocket objections with plain English triggers & scripts.
When. Depositions, hearings, and trial.

Cards
â€¢	Relevance â†’ â€œObjection, relevance; move to strike as not probative of any element.â€
â€¢	Hearsay â†’ â€œObjection, hearsay; not within an exception.â€
â€¢	Foundation â†’ â€œObjection, lack of foundation; witness has not established [X].â€
â€¢	Assumes Facts Not in Evidence â†’ â€œObjection, assumes facts not in evidence.â€
â€¢	Speculation â†’ â€œObjection, calls for speculation.â€
â€¢	Privilege â†’ â€œObjection, attorney client/work product; I decline to answer.â€

Pitfalls
â€¢ Speaking objections; arguing with the examiner on record.
Cross Refs. FG 600s (Exposure), JC Evidence filters, LCa Daubert & In Limine.
 
9.4 Discovery Request Builder (RFPs/Interrogatories)

Purpose. Draft precise discovery tied to elements; resist boilerplate objections.
When. Early discovery planning; pre PI limited discovery; post MTD scheduling.

Checklist
â€¢	Chart each claim â†’ element(s) â†’ fact gap â†’ request
â€¢	Define timeframe & custodians
â€¢	Use definitions & instructions to pre empt evasions
â€¢	Add RFP/ROG pairs: document first, then interrogatory to explain

Model Requests (Retaliation example)
â€¢	RFP 1: â€œAll communications (email, text, Teams/Slack) between [names] from [date1â€“date2] that reference [protected activity/you].â€
â€¢	ROG 1: â€œIdentify each adverse action taken against Plaintiff between [date1â€“date2], including decision makers, date, and stated reason.â€

Pitfalls
â€¢ Overbroad universals; undefined terms; no timeframe; no custodians.
Cross Refs. LC Elements mapping; LCa ESI narrowing; JC Proportionality cudgel.

Field Card (print)
â€¢	Element â†’ Fact Gap â†’ Request.
â€¢	Timeframe + Custodian + Format.
â€¢	Pair RFP with a confirming Interrogatory.
 
