9.1 Annotated Motion â€” Before & After

Common mistake (Before)

â€œPlaintiff respectfully requests appropriate relief in light of the equities and asks the Court to do justice in this matter.â€

Reframed (After)

â€œPlaintiff moves under Rule 37(a) for an order compelling production of Items Aâ€“C identified in RFP 3 (served 08/14/25) because Defendant failed to produce by 09/01/25 and the items are proportional and central to Element 2 (causation). See Ex. A (RFP 3); Ex. B (meet and confer email 09/03/25).â€

Pattern to copy
Rule â†’ Specific relief â†’ Dated record cites â†’ Element mapping â†’ Narrow scope
 
9.4 Discovery Request Builder â€” Before & After

Vague RFP (Before)

â€œAll documents regarding Plaintiff.â€

Precise RFP (After)

â€œAll emails, texts, and Teams/Slack messages between Krouner and Shipley from 08/01/2025â€“09/30/2025 that reference Plaintiff, the August 19 meeting, or the September 6 meeting. Custodians: Krouner, Shipley, HR Director. Formats: PST/MSG/CSV. Search terms: [list].â€

ROG pairing

â€œIdentify each adverse action considered or taken 08/01/2025â€“09/30/2025, with decision maker, date, and stated reason; cite supporting documents by Bates range.â€
 
9.7 Responding to Discovery (Objections & Answers)

Purpose. Answer opponent RFPs/Interrogatories without waiving rights; make clean objections; commit to rolling production when appropriate.
When. Within response window after service (check local rules).
Quick Win. Use specific objections tied to scope/time/custodian; avoid shotgun/boilerplate.

Checklist
â€¢	Calendar the response deadline; request extension if needed
â€¢	Read definitions; confirm terms/custodians/timeframes
â€¢	Draft specific objections (scope/time/burden/privilege)
â€¢	Answer to the extent not objectionable
â€¢	State whether responsive documents exist and whether you will produce
â€¢	If withholding for privilege/protection, provide privilege log

Objection bank (plain English + script)
â€¢	Overbroad/time: â€œObjection; time period not limited. Without waiving, we answer for 01/01/2024â€“present.â€
â€¢	Unduly burdensome/custodian: â€œObjection; requests all custodians without limit. We will search Krouner, Shipley, HR Director.â€
â€¢	Vague/ambiguous: â€œObjection; vague as to â€˜communications.â€™ We construe this as email/text/Teams/Slack.â€
â€¢	Premature expert: â€œObjection to contention expert analysis; premature under schedule.â€
â€¢	Privilege/Work product: â€œResponsive material exists but is withheld as attorney client/work product; see Privilege Log.â€

Template â€” RFP Responses
PLAINTIFFâ€™S RESPONSES & OBJECTIONS TO DEFENDANTâ€™S FIRST RFPs

General Objections are **not** incorporated; objections are made per item.

RFP 1: [quoted]
Response: Objection â€” [specific]. Without waiving, Plaintiff will produce nonâ€‘privileged
emails and texts from 08/01/2025â€“09/30/2025 for custodians Krouner, Shipley, HR Director,
subject to protective order. Production on a rolling basis beginning 10/10/2025.
