9.8 Mediation & Settlement Pack

Purpose. Prepare for mediation; evaluate offers; draft a term sheet that survives.
When. Court ordered mediation; party initiated settlement talks; after key rulings.
Quick Win. Arrive with a one page term sheet and a BATNA/WATNA score.

Mediation Prep Checklist
â€¢	Confidential mediation statement (facts, issues, obstacles, prior offers)
â€¢	Must haves vs nice to haves; walk away number
â€¢	Non monetary terms (references, neutral statement, training, policy changes)
â€¢	Authority/attendance confirmed; time blocks calendared

Term Sheet â€” Template
Parties; Effective date; Consideration ($ and nonâ€‘$); Payment schedule; Tax language; 
Scope of release (claims/parties/timeframe); Dismissal form (with/without prejudice);
No admission clause; Confidentiality (if any); Nonâ€‘disparagement (scope/term);
Nonâ€‘retaliation; Neutral reference language; Confidential return of property/records;
Enforcement jurisdiction; Mutual fee/costs terms; Signatures; Execution deadline.
Parties; Effective date; Consideration ($ and non $); Payment schedule; Tax language; 
Scope of release (claims/parties/timeframe); Dismissal form (with/without prejudice);
No admission clause; Confidentiality (if any); Non disparagement (scope/term);
Non retaliation; Neutral reference language; Confidential return of property/records;
Enforcement jurisdiction; Mutual fee/costs terms; Signatures; Execution deadline.
Evaluation Worksheet
Offer amount; probability of success; time to judgment; costs; risk bands; present value calculator (note: add simple spreadsheet in repo).

Opening (60 seconds)

â€œWeâ€™re here to resolve [issues] efficiently. Our proposal centers on [narrow, dated harms] with [specific remedy]; weâ€™re open to structure if the core terms are met.â€

Pitfalls
â€¢ Vague releases; missing enforcement clause; hidden tax implications.
Cross Refs. LCa Remedies & Settlement Â· FG Continuity/Coalition.
 
