Glossary (Plain English)
â€¢	Dispositive motion: Asks the court to decide claims without trial (e.g., MTD, summary judgment).
â€¢	Pro se: Representing yourself without a lawyer.
â€¢	Plausibility: The 12(b)(6) standardâ€”facts must make the claim believable on its face.
â€¢	Safe harbor: Rule window to correct a filing before sanctions are sought.
â€¢	Certificate of Service (COS): Proof of who/what/when/how you served.
â€¢	Meet and confer: Required attempt to resolve disputes before moving the court.
â€¢	Privilege log: Table describing withheld documents (date/author/recipients/privilege).
â€¢	Protective Order (PO)/AEO: Court order restricting use of sensitive discovery (â€œAttorneysâ€™ Eyes Onlyâ€).
â€¢	TRO/PI: Temporary Restraining Order/Preliminary Injunctionâ€”early injunctive relief.
 
